Terminal Velocity is a 1994 action film starring Charlie Sheen as a daredevil skydiver who becomes mixed up with Russian spies. It was written by David Twohy and directed by Deran Sarafian. The film co-stars Nastassja Kinski, James Gandolfini and Christopher McDonald.Originally, Sheen's role was written for Tom Cruise, although Michael Douglas and William Baldwin were also considered. The script itself sold for US $500,000. The musical score was composed by Joel McNeely.
